<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-04-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="965" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d965">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/7071.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to
                                    Chile</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-04-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs informs me that the action of Chile in
                            regard to recognition of the Mexican Government will largely conform to
                            that of the United States.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>